  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving the Nutrition of People Recovering from Drug Addiction and People Living with HIV/AIDS (PLWHA) in Kirovohrad Oblast through Greenhouse Development</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Heifer will assist over 200 clients of the Ukrainian Kirovohrad Oblast Rehabilitation Center in a three-stage project involving the provision of two or more greenhouses, rabbits, vegetable, fruit and berry seeds, and training in enterprise development. By setting up greenhouses and mini rabbit breeding farms at the rehabilitation center, Heifer Ukraine will work with partners to ensure that by 2012, at least 200 clients will have improved their quality of life and nutrition. Additionally, through their work on the Heifer project, at least 27 clients of the rehabilitation center will acquire new knowledge and skills every year, thus complimenting the therapeutic effects of the rehabilitation center&#x2019;s re-socialization program. An additional 27 residents of the center will benefit from the project each year, through a continuous &#x201C;passing on the gift&#x201D; process. By 2012, the rehabilitation center&#x2019;s income levels are expected to have increased by 15 percent from the sale of green vegetables, fruits and berries, rabbit meat and fur, gradually making the center self-reliant and independent of donor funding, while at the same time, developing entrepreneurship skills among the recovering clients.</narrative>
  </description>
